      "side": 1,
      "message": "So your issue is that you need `xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Decorator.Asset` interface on the actual inventory item (held by EM) instead of the object that the vpd parser produces.\n\nDoes your probe statement look like this by any chance?\n\n```\n    \"Name\": \"chassis\",\n    \"Probe\": \"xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Decorator.Asset({\u0027Model\u0027: \u0027HPE ProLiant DL365 Gen11\u0027})\",\n    \"Type\": \"Chassis\",\n    \"xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Decorator.Asset\": {\n        \"Manufacturer\": \"$Manufacturer\",\n        \"Model\": \"$Model\",\n        \"PartNumber\": \"$PartNumber\",\n        \"SerialNumber\": \"$SerialNumber\"\n    },\n```\n\nTo solve the immediate issue, is it possible to slightly change the property value of what you are probing on vs. what you expose?\n\n\ne.g.\n\n`    \"Probe\": \n\"xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Decorator.Asset(\n{\u0027Model\u0027: \u0027HPE ProLiant DL365 Gen11-probe\u0027})\",`",
